#. <section class="sutta" id="sn18.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn18.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 18"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 18"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn18.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 1. Cakkhusutta → cakkhuādisuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn18.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Cakkhusutta"
msgstr "1. The Eye, Etc."

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "sn18.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "sn18.1:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn18.1:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rāhulo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Rāhula went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:1.4"
msgid "“sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā saṃkhittena dhammaṃ desetu, yamahaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ sutvā eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto vihareyyan”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, may the Buddha please teach me Dhamma in brief. When I’ve heard it, I’ll live alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.245"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn18.1:2.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Rāhula? "

msgctxt "sn18.1:2.2"
msgid "cakkhuṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:2.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:2.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:2.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:2.6"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn18.1:2.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:2.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn18.1:3.1"
msgid "“Sotaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is the ear permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:3.2"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” …"

msgctxt "sn18.1:3.3"
msgid "“Ghānaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is the nose permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:3.4"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” …"
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” …"

msgctxt "sn18.1:3.5"
msgid "“Jivhā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is the tongue permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:3.6"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante” …"
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” …"

msgctxt "sn18.1:3.7"
msgid "“Kāyo nicco vā anicco vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is the body permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:3.8"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante” …"
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” …"

msgctxt "sn18.1:3.9"
msgid "“Mano nicco vā anicco vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is the mind permanent or impermanent?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:3.10"
msgid "“Anicco, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

msgctxt "sn18.1:3.11"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:3.12"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:3.13"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn18.1:3.14"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn18.1:3.15"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p class="added">
# In this and similar passages, the handling of abbreviations in MS seems to be incorrect. When dealing with extended sets of phenomena associated with the ayatana, ellipsis is required. Here, however, the text deals only with the interior ayatanas—eye, ear, nose, etc. So there seems to be no call for ellipsis, and the practice is inherited incorrectly. Nevertheless, as it doesn’t affect the meaning, I don’t change the text.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn18.1:4.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati … pe … sotasmimpi nibbindati … ghānasmimpi nibbindati … jivhāyapi nibbindati … kāyasmimpi nibbindati … manasmimpi nibbindati;"
msgstr "“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, the ear, the nose, the tongue, the body, and the mind."

msgctxt "sn18.1:4.2"
msgid "nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn18.1:4.3"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti."
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”"

msgctxt "sn18.1:4.4"
msgid "(Etena peyyālena dasa suttantā kātabbā.)"
msgstr "(The ten discourses of this series should be treated in the same way.)"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn18.1:4.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
